  "prompt": "How you say lover in Hindi?",
  "response": "In Hindi, the word for \"lover\" can vary depending on the context. Here are a few common terms:\n\n1. \u092a\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0930 \u0915\u0930\u0928\u0947 \u0935\u093e\u0932\u093e/\u0935\u093e\u0932\u0940 (Pyaar Karne Waala/Waali) - Literally means \"the one who loves.\"\n2. \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u092e\u0940 (Premi) - This is often used for a male lover.\n3. \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u092e\u093f\u0915\u093e (Premika) - This is used for a female lover.\n4. \u0938\u093e\u0925\u0940 (Saathi) - Can mean \"partner\" or \"companion,\" and is sometimes used in a romantic context.\n5. \u091c\u093e\u0928 (Jaan) - A term of endearment meaning \"life\" or \"beloved.\"\n\nEach term can be used in different contexts, so the choice of word may depend on the specific situation or the nuance you want to convey.",
